                <head>18. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The National Security Council’s 303 Committee and its successor, the 40
                    Committee, reviewed proposals for major and/or politically sensitive covert
                    action programs. For documentation on the 303 Committee and the 40 Committee, as
                    well as on the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Intelligence Committee and
                    the Net Assessment Group within the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Staff,
                    both of which were established on November 5, 1971, see <ref target="#d92"
                        >Documents 92</ref>, <ref target="#d182">182</ref>, <ref target="#d184"
                        >184</ref>, <ref target="#d185">185</ref>, <ref target="#d189">189</ref>,
                        <ref target="#d195">195</ref>, <ref target="#d203">203</ref>, <ref
                        target="#d218">218</ref>, <ref target="#d228">228</ref>, <ref target="#d239"
                        >239</ref>, <ref target="#d242">242</ref>–<ref target="#d247">47</ref>, <ref
                        target="#d250">250</ref>, <ref target="#d251">251</ref>, <ref target="#d256"
                        >256</ref>, <ref target="#d265">265</ref>, <ref target="#d266">266</ref>,
                        <ref target="#d268">268</ref>, <ref target="#d270">270</ref>, <ref
                        target="#d278">278</ref>, <ref target="#d279">279</ref>, <ref target="#d286"
                        >286</ref>, and <ref target="#d287">287</ref>.</p>
            </div>
